---
title: Morning Dew
date: "2025-07-09"
description: "A poem about the quiet beauty of dawn"
---

# Morning Dew

Silver droplets on emerald blades,
Tiny worlds reflecting the dawn.
Each sphere a universe unto itself,
Ephemeral treasures soon gone.

The morning light filters through trees,
Casting shadows long and deep.
As the world slowly awakens,
From its restful, dreamless sleep.

I walk through this glistening landscape,
My footprints marking the way.
Each step disturbing the perfect balance,
Of nature's delicate display.

How fleeting this moment of beauty,
How transient this perfect scene.
By midday the dew will vanish,
Leaving no trace of where it's been.

Yet tomorrow it will return anew,
Fresh droplets on waiting leaves.
A daily reminder of life's cycles,
And the joy that morning weaves.
